</nav>

<!-- ── Hero ── -->
<div class="uc-hero">
  <div class="section-tag" style="justify-content:center;margin-bottom:20px">use cases</div>
  <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.6rem);max-width:700px;margin:0 auto 16px">What you can build<br/>with <span class="gradient-text">JamJet</span></h1>
  <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:1.05rem;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto">
    Real production patterns — from multi-agent A2A pipelines to durable human-in-the-loop
    workflows. Each use case links to working code you can run today.
  </p>
</div>

<hr class="sep"/>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- FEATURED: Investment Due Diligence                                    -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="padding: 64px 24px">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="case-hero">

      <div class="case-eyebrow">Featured case study &nbsp;·&nbsp; A2A protocol &nbsp;·&nbsp; RAG &nbsp;·&nbsp; Parallel agents</div>

      <h2 class="case-title">Investment Due Diligence<br/>with a Network of Specialized Agents</h2>

      <p class="case-lead">
        A single company name triggers a parallel network of three specialized AI agents —
        each an independent HTTP service speaking the A2A protocol — that collaborates to
        produce a complete investment due diligence report: financials, market positioning,
        risk scorecard, and investment recommendation.
      </p>

      <!-- Metrics -->
      <div class="metrics-row">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">1.74×</div>
          <div class="metric-label">parallel speedup over sequential</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">3</div>
          <div class="metric-label">specialized agents, zero shared memory</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">&lt;5ms</div>
          <div class="metric-label">RAG retrieval per query</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">12</div>
          <div class="metric-label">A2A HTTP round-trips total</div>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <div class="metric-num">~6s</div>
          <div class="metric-label">wall-clock time, full report</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Architecture flow -->
      <h3 style="font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:16px">Architecture</h3>

      <div class="arch-block">┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  VC Analyst: <span style="color:var(--yellow)">python run.py Anthropic</span>                          │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
                           ▼
           ┌───────────────────────────────┐
           │       Orchestrator            │
           │   (pure HTTP — no imports     │
           │    from agent modules)        │
           └──────┬─────────────┬──────────┘
                  │             │  Phase 2: submit tasks in parallel
    ┌─────────────▼─┐       ┌───▼─────────────┐
    │ Financial Agent│       │  Market Agent   │
    │    :7701       │       │     :7702       │
    │                │       │                 │
    │  RAG pipeline: │       │  RAG pipeline:  │
    │  financials.md │       │  markets.md     │
    │  → chunk →     │       │  → chunk →      │
    │  score →       │       │  score →        │
    │  retrieve →    │       │  retrieve →     │
    │  LLM           │       │  LLM            │
    └────────┬───────┘       └────────┬────────┘
             │                        │
             └──────────┬─────────────┘
                        │  Phase 4: combine + send to Risk Agent
                        ▼
           ┌────────────────────────────┐
           │       Risk Agent  :7703    │
           │                            │
           │  6-dimension risk rubric   │
           │  + LLM synthesis           │
           │  → scorecard + rating      │
           └─────────────┬──────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
          Full Due Diligence Report
    (Financial + Market + Risk Score + Recommendation)</div>

      <!-- Two-column body -->
      <div class="case-body">
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why A2A here — not a single agent</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Financial and market analysis are <strong>independent</strong> — parallel A2A cuts wall-clock time by 42%</li>
            <li>Each agent optimizes its own <strong>system prompt and temperature</strong> for its domain — a single LLM call can't do both well</li>
            <li>Swapping the Market Agent for a <strong>PitchBook integration</strong> is one URL change — no orchestrator code changes</li>
            <li>Each agent is a <strong>separate HTTP service</strong> — deployable to separate infrastructure, independently scalable</li>
            <li>A third-party agent from another team or company can <strong>plug in via A2A</strong> — no SDK sharing needed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="body-block">
          <h3>Why RAG — not live web search</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Web-scraped financial figures are <strong>inconsistent across sources</strong> — a curated knowledge base gives internally consistent data</li>
            <li><strong>LLMs hallucinate specific numbers</strong> without grounding — RAG forces reasoning over real data</li>
            <li>RAG retrieval from local docs is <strong>&lt;5ms</strong> — web search adds 2–5s per query</li>
            <li>In production, financial data comes from <strong>signed data agreements</strong> (PitchBook, Bloomberg) — web scraping doesn't replace that</li>
            <li>Swap from keyword overlap to <strong>vector embeddings</strong> by replacing one function — the interface is the same</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How the A2A protocol works -->
      <div style="margin-top: 48px">
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:16px">How the A2A protocol works in this example</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:20px">
          Each agent exposes exactly three endpoints. The orchestrator uses only these — no Python imports, no shared memory, no coupled deployment.
        </p>

        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:16px;margin-bottom:28px">
          <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border-sub);border-radius:8px;padding:20px">
            <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--yellow);margin-bottom:8px">GET /.well-known/agent.json</div>
            <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-muted)">Agent Card — name, description, version, capabilities, skill IDs. The orchestrator fetches all three in parallel at startup.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border-sub);border-radius:8px;padding:20px">
            <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--yellow);margin-bottom:8px">POST /a2a/tasks</div>
            <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-muted)">Submit a task with a skill_id and input. The agent returns a task_id immediately and processes asynchronously.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border-sub);border-radius:8px;padding:20px">
            <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--yellow);margin-bottom:8px">GET /a2a/tasks/{'{id}'}</div>
            <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-muted)">Poll for result. Status: pending → running → complete. The orchestrator polls all agents concurrently using asyncio.gather().</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Agent card JSON -->
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">
            <span>Agent Card — Financial Research Agent</span>
            <span>JSON</span>
          </div>
          <div class="code-body">{`{
  "id": "financial-agent",
  "name": "Financial Research Agent",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "url": "http://localhost:7701",
  "skills": [
    {
      "id": "analyze_financials",
      "name": "Analyze Financials",
      "description": "RAG-powered financial analysis over curated knowledge base",
      "inputModes": ["text"],
      "outputModes": ["text"]
    }
  ]
}`}</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Orchestrator code -->
        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:16px">
          <div class="code-header">
            <span>orchestrator.py — parallel task submission + polling</span>
            <span>Python</span>
          </div>
          <div class="code-body"><span class="c-c"># Submit Financial + Market tasks in parallel</span>
<span class="c-n">fin_task</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-n">mkt_task</span> <span class="c-p">=</span> <span class="c-k">await</span> asyncio<span class="c-p">.</span><span class="c-f">gather</span><span class="c-p">(</span>
    <span class="c-n">session</span><span class="c-p">.</span><span class="c-f">post</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-s">f"&#123;FIN_URL&#125;/a2a/tasks"</span><span class="c-p">,</span> json<span class="c-p">=</span><span class="c-p">&#123;</span><span class="c-s">"skill_id"</span><span class="c-p">:</span> <span class="c-s">"analyze_financials"</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-s">"input"</span><span class="c-p">:</span> query<span class="c-p">&#125;</span><span class="c-p">)</span><span class="c-p">,</span>
    <span class="c-n">session</span><span class="c-p">.</span><span class="c-f">post</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-s">f"&#123;MKT_URL&#125;/a2a/tasks"</span><span class="c-p">,</span> json<span class="c-p">=</span><span class="c-p">&#123;</span><span class="c-s">"skill_id"</span><span class="c-p">:</span> <span class="c-s">"analyze_market"</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-s">"input"</span><span class="c-p">:</span> query<span class="c-p">&#125;</span><span class="c-p">)</span><span class="c-p">,</span>
<span class="c-p">)</span>

<span class="c-c"># Poll both concurrently until complete</span>
<span class="c-k">async def</span> <span class="c-f">poll</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-n">base_url</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-n">task_id</span><span class="c-p">):</span>
    <span class="c-k">while</span> <span class="c-k">True</span><span class="c-p">:</span>
        <span class="c-n">data</span> <span class="c-p">=</span> <span class="c-k">await</span> <span class="c-f">get_json</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-s">f"&#123;base_url&#125;/a2a/tasks/&#123;task_id&#125;"</span><span class="c-p">)</span>
        <span class="c-k">if</span> <span class="c-n">data</span><span class="c-p">[</span><span class="c-s">"status"</span><span class="c-p">]</span> <span class="c-p">==</span> <span class="c-s">"complete"</span><span class="c-p">:</span>
            <span class="c-k">return</span> <span class="c-n">data</span><span class="c-p">[</span><span class="c-s">"output"</span><span class="c-p">]</span>
        <span class="c-k">await</span> asyncio<span class="c-p">.</span><span class="c-f">sleep</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-s">0.5</span><span class="c-p">)</span>

<span class="c-n">financial</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-n">market</span> <span class="c-p">=</span> <span class="c-k">await</span> asyncio<span class="c-p">.</span><span class="c-f">gather</span><span class="c-p">(</span>
    <span class="c-f">poll</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-n">FIN_URL</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-n">fin_task</span><span class="c-p">),</span>
    <span class="c-f">poll</span><span class="c-p">(</span><span class="c-n">MKT_URL</span><span class="c-p">,</span> <span class="c-n">mkt_task</span><span class="c-p">),</span>
<span class="c-p">)</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Timing comparison -->
      <div style="margin-top:48px">
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:16px">Sequential vs parallel — what the benchmark shows</h3>
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:20px">
          <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--error);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;opacity:0.7">
            <div style="font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:var(--error);margin-bottom:12px">Sequential (naive monolith)</div>
            <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:2">
              Financial analysis: 1,842ms<br/>
              Market analysis:    2,104ms<br/>
              Risk synthesis:     3,211ms<br/>
              <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">──────────────────────────</span><br/>
              <span style="color:var(--error)">Total: ~7,157ms</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--success);border-radius:8px;padding:24px">
            <div style="font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:var(--success);margin-bottom:12px">Parallel A2A (JamJet)</div>
            <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:2">
              Financial ┐<br/>
              Market    ┘ max(1842, 2104) = 2,104ms<br/>
              Risk synthesis:     3,211ms<br/>
              <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">──────────────────────────</span><br/>
              <span style="color:var(--success)">Total: ~5,315ms &nbsp;(1.74× faster)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:0.78rem;color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:12px">
          Speedup grows as you add more parallel agents. 5 independent agents → ~4× faster than sequential.
          Figures from a real run against Vertex AI (Gemini Flash).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Try it -->
      <div style="margin-top:48px;padding:28px;background:var(--yellow-dim);border:1px solid var(--yellow);border-radius:8px">
        <div style="font-size:0.78rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:var(--yellow);margin-bottom:12px">Run it yourself</div>
        <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text);line-height:2">
          pip install aiohttp openai<br/>
          git clone https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples<br/>
          cd examples/due-diligence<br/>
          <span style="color:var(--text-muted)"># Set OPENAI_API_KEY (or use Vertex AI / Ollama)</span><br/>
          python run.py Anthropic
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:16px;display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
