        <p>Support tickets touch multiple systems — CRM, billing, ticketing — and need human escalation for edge cases. A single crash can lose context mid-resolution.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>Durable graph execution — resume after crash, no context lost</span>
          <span>Human-in-the-loop escalation as a first-class workflow node</span>
          <span>MCP tools for CRM, Zendesk, Stripe — no custom API wrappers</span>
          <span>Event timeline for every resolution — full audit trail</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uc-card">
        <div class="uc-card-icon">🔍</div>
        <h3>Autonomous Code Review</h3>
        <div class="tagline">Critic strategy + eval harness in CI</div>
        <p>Code review agents that draft feedback, critique their own output, and revise — then score quality against a rubric before posting. Catch low-quality reviews before they reach developers.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>Critic strategy — draft → self-critique → revise loop</span>
          <span>Eval harness with LLM-judge scorer gating the CI step</span>
          <span>MCP tools to read diffs, run linters, query test results</span>
          <span>Cost and iteration limits enforced at compile time</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uc-card">
        <div class="uc-card-icon">📊</div>
        <h3>Research & Report Generation</h3>
        <div class="tagline">Plan-and-execute over long-horizon tasks</div>
        <p>Long-horizon research tasks — market reports, competitive analyses, literature reviews — that need structured plans, multiple tool calls, and synthesis across many sources.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>Plan-and-execute strategy — structured plan first, then steps</span>
          <span>MCP tools for web search, document retrieval, scraping</span>
          <span>OTel traces show exact token cost per research step</span>
          <span>Resumable — pause a 10-step report mid-way, continue later</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uc-card">
        <div class="uc-card-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Multi-Agent Data Pipelines</h3>
        <div class="tagline">Independent extractors in parallel, one synthesizer</div>
        <p>Data extraction pipelines where multiple independent sources are queried in parallel — pricing, inventory, compliance — before a synthesis agent aggregates the results.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>A2A parallel delegation — multiple extractor agents at once</span>
          <span>Each extractor is a separate service — independently deployable</span>
          <span>Typed state schemas — no stringly-typed data passing</span>
          <span>Agent Cards enable dynamic discovery of new data sources</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uc-card">
        <div class="uc-card-icon">✅</div>
        <h3>Compliance & Risk Review</h3>
        <div class="tagline">Human approval gates with durable state</div>
        <p>Regulated workflows that require human sign-off at specific checkpoints. The agent stops, waits for approval via API or webhook, then resumes — surviving restarts while suspended.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>Human-in-the-loop node — durably paused, not polling</span>
          <span>Resume via API call, CLI, or webhook — no manual state restoration</span>
          <span>Event sourcing — every decision has a full audit trail</span>
          <span>Policy engine — enforced tool allowlists per agent role</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uc-card">
        <div class="uc-card-icon">🌐</div>
        <h3>Cross-Framework Agent Networks</h3>
        <div class="tagline">JamJet agents next to LangChain, AutoGen, or SaaS agents</div>
        <p>Your org runs different agent frameworks in different teams. A2A lets JamJet agents interoperate with LangChain agents, AutoGen agents, or any SaaS agent that speaks the protocol.</p>
        <div class="features">
          <span>A2A client — call any A2A-compatible agent as a workflow node</span>
          <span>A2A server — expose JamJet agents to external orchestrators</span>
          <span>Language-agnostic — agents can be Python, Rust, TypeScript, or Go</span>
          <span>Agent Cards — standard capability discovery across orgs</span>
        </div>
      </div>

